<br>
My brief idea: Points should only be obtained from people your  5 or so levels beneath you or higher, prorated for disparity in levels.  You should not lose or gain points for kills below the point enabled level limit.  Leave the insignias and coin the way they are.  I believe this system would more accurately reflect who the best pkillers are.  I work from an assumption (disputed by Grim and others) that point systems don't really show you who's winning in terms of the overall deity war, but could show you who is doing the best individually as pkillers when faced with a real challenge.  This would also remove the focus on green farming.  I think killing greens does have its place in this war, but should have nothing to do with point totals.  Killing low greens has nothing to do with pvp skill, but everything to do with helping your team win the war, and thus should not be reflected in the point system (which also has nothing to do with winning the war).<br>
<br>
My second adjustment would be to change the awarding of points and kill credit.  I would only reward points/insignias to people and groups that do over 50% of the target's HP max for the current level, rather than their current HP or the overly simplistic killing blow technique.  For a group to gain points, each individual member would need to be able to get points from the kill had they done so individually.  There are many ramifications from this approach, most of them positive in my opinion.  There could be some chicanery with removing buffs or gear to manipulate the HP amount, but I think the effects of that would be negligable.  What is gained is the ability to award group points to be distributed among all in the group that did the necessary damage in a way similar to how experience is rewarded - thus rewarding those support classes who participate.  It also would make the red/white buddy system point farming much more tedious, hopefully discouraging it for the most part.  The hate list or table for a given pc under attack would be smaller than it would be if the current npc hate list mechanics were used, as anyone incapable of having caused 50% total hp damage would not be carried on the table (this seems to be the main argument for why Verant doesn't just use the exp calculation mechanism for pk point assignment, they don't want to attach lengthy hate list structures to pc's).  This would possibly create the capability to be acredited with a kill even if the player zones and is killed by something/someone else - although I don't know if Verant could keep the hate list from being scrubbed on a zone.  Also it would remove undue credit for cheapy kills - removing one motivation for picking off non-challenging targets.  <br>
<br>
<br>
